    <div class="col-md-8">
      <div class="hero-explanation">
        <p>The EPA and Robert Wood Johnson Foundation estimate there are as many as 5,000,000 homes in New England with Lead or Galvanized pipes that periodically contaminate your water.</p>

        <p>Typically, the lead is contained in the solder connecting the <em>service pipes</em> that carry the water from the municipal water pipes, which run under your street.</p>

        <p>We specialize in testing the service pipes of homes built before 1986, the year when amendments to the <a target="_blank" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2509614/">Safe Drinking Water Act</a> prohibited the installment of lead pipes nationwide.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
